{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8f25b4",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Neuropathy, proteinuria, hepatomegaly, periorbital ecchymosis, bruising, and low-voltage ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"electrocardiogram",
"children":[
"ECG"
]
},
" despite increased ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"left ventricular",
"children":[
"LV"
]
},
" hypertrophy. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cardiac magnetic resonance (imaging)",
"children":[
"CMR"
]
},
" imaging will support the diagnosis but not differentiate AL amyloidosis from hereditary transthyretin amyloidosis. A positive technetium pyrophosphate scan is diagnostic of hereditary transthyretin amyloidosis. In patients with AL amyloidosis, diagnosis can often be confirmed with abdominal fat pad aspiration."
]
},
" "
]
}
